Release history for Plack-Middleware-Rewrite

2.102 Sun 04 Sep 2022
	- Proper support of 304 responses: they are no longer treated as redirects
	- No more parent.pm dependency
	- Updated packaging and package metadata

2.101 Mon 26 Feb 2018
	- Minor documentation copyedit and packaging fix

2.100 Mon 26 Feb 2018
	- Response status code rewriting support

2.000 Thu 14 May 2015
	- New interface with separate `request`/`response` rewrite callbacks,
	  with unambiguous return value protocol, which supports redirecting
	  to different PSGI apps
	- Full legacy interface support for `rules` callback

1.101 Sat 14 Mar 2015
	- No functional changes
	- Test suite fixes and refactoring

1.100 Sun 01 Mar 2015
	- Response body filter support

1.010 Fri 09 Jan 2015
	- No functional changes
	- Test suite cleanup
	- Minimum Perl requirement declared

1.009 Fri 02 Jan 2015
	- Explicit documentation of how to redirect to a different host (OALDERS)

1.008 Fri 28 Feb 2014
	- Fix for XSS test

1.007 Tue 12 Feb 2013
	- Default body in middleware-generated redirect responses

1.006 Thu 27 Dec 2012
	- Fix for buggy interaction with streaming

1.005 Thu 07 Jun 2012
	- Pre-existing Location header in fabricated responses now preserved

1.004 Thu 29 Mar 2012
	- External redirects preserve query params (by dropping unnecessary use of URI)
	  (with thanks to Wallace Reis)

1.003 Tue 01 Mar 2011
	- No functional changes
	- Dependecy on Plack 0.9942 declared

1.002 Fri 18 Feb 2011
	- Now uses `response_cb`

1.001 Thu 17 Feb 2011
	- No functional changes
	- Dependencies declared

1.0 Wed 16 Feb 2011
	- Initial release
